title: DBIO::Test::Schema::ArtistGUID a_guid column uses wrong attribute for non-PK GUID auto-population
description: 
The ported ArtistGUID schema in dbio core has the wrong attribute on the non-PK `a_guid` column. It uses `is_auto_increment => 1` but should use `auto_nextval => 1`.

Background:
- `DBIO::Storage::DBI::UniqueIdentifier::_prefetch_autovalues` only triggers on `auto_nextval => 1` for non-PK GUID columns (see the `@auto_guids` grep at line 85-91 of UniqueIdentifier.pm)
- The PK column `artistid` is handled by a separate code path (`@pk_guids`) that does NOT need any flag
- The test in dbio-mssql t/11-mssql-odbc.t (and presumably t/10, t/20, t/21) expects a non-PK `a_guid` to be auto-populated with a NEWID() value

Current (wrong) schema at lib/DBIO/Test/Schema/ArtistGUID.pm lines 27-32:
  a_guid => {
    data_type => 'uniqueidentifier',
    is_nullable => 1,
    is_auto_increment => 1,
  },

The test (t/11-mssql-odbc.t line 453-457) checks that the row's `a_guid` is populated:
  ok(
    eval { $row->a_guid },
    'row has a GUID col with auto_nextval populated',
  );

This is failing because `is_auto_increment` is not checked by UniqueIdentifier's prefetch logic for non-PK columns.

Fix: change `is_auto_increment => 1` to `auto_nextval => 1` on line 30 of lib/DBIO/Test/Schema/ArtistGUID.pm.

Cross-reference: the upstream MigrationsTest/Schema/ArtistGUID.pm in dbio/t/lib/ uses `auto_nextval => 1` for `a_guid` (see comment: "auto_nextval not necessary for PK" / "necessary here, because not a PK").

Context: This was discovered while running live integration tests against MSSQL 2022 in k3s (dbio-mssql t/11-mssql-odbc.t). 121/123 tests pass after the dbio-mssql Storage.pm fix and test fixes, but test 113 fails because of this schema attribute mismatch.
Resolved upstream in dbio core ticket #20, commit 31064788 (2026-06-10): a_guid now auto_nextval => 1, matching upstream MigrationsTest schema. Core dzil-installed locally — re-run t/11-mssql-odbc.t (test 113) to verify.
